race.description: Cuprum Distillery - South West Stormy Mdn
race.comment: PUBLICISE (11) was well held fresh then made a much improved run at Ascot when led and was run down late. Looks well placed here and is the one to catch. LONG LAUGH (2) has placed two of four starts and has been going well at big odds. On speed third two back at Belmont before finishing fourth and beaten only a length at Northam last time. Back up in trip and expected to go close. EXTREME RULER (1) is long overdue and has placed last three on end. Third here last time over seven furlongs and off a freshen should run well this company. MORE THEN HARD (4) had one run in first campaign which was better than it looked when ninth at Ascot over 1400m. Blinkers added for return and presents on the back of two trials. RED ZED (7) is an interesting first starter. Never raced but was in work in NZ with several trials then switched yards and has been trialling very well for new barn. Watch the betting closely.
